---
description: "Testing + quality gates (Laravel feature tests, critical auction flows)"
globs:
  - "**/*.php"
  - "**/*.ts"
  - "**/*.tsx"
  - "**/*.js"
  - "**/*.jsx"
---

## Backend testing (Laravel)
- For any new API route, add at least one **Feature test**.
- Critical flows MUST have tests:
  - register/login/logout
  - create listing
  - start/end auction
  - place bid (accept)
  - place bid (reject: too low, after end, self-bid)
  - concurrent bid behavior (at least one test that proves atomicity/locking)

## Frontend testing (lightweight by default)
- If a testing setup exists, add smoke tests for:
  - listing details renders
  - bidding form validates and handles errors

## Quality gates
- No secret files committed (`.env`, keys).
- Keep API error responses consistent and documented.
- Every PR/change should include a brief manual test plan:
  - what URL/page to open
  - what action to take
  - expected outcome
